        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: default cron runMode to \"due\" instead of \"force\" (#94270)",
        "body": "## Description\n\nWhen the `runMode` parameter is omitted from a cron \"run\" action, the default value now respects schedule guards (`\"due\"`) instead of bypassing them (`\"force\"`). This prevents unintended execution of scheduled jobs outside their configured time windows. Fixes a P1 security issue where bare cron run bypassed all schedule guards.\n\n## Changes\n- **`src/agents/tools/cron-tool.ts`**: 1-line change: default `runMode` fallback from `\"force\"` to `\"due\"`\n- **`src/agents/tools/cron-tool.test.ts`**: Updated expectations from `mode: \"force\"` to `mode: \"due\"`\n\n## Related Issue\nFixes #94270\n\n## AI Assistance\nThis PR was created with assistance from AI (Claude Code).\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n### Environment\n- **Platform:** Linux x86_64, OpenClaw Gateway v1.8.0 (production instance)\n- **Node.js:** v22.22.0\n- **Branch:** fix/cron-runmode-default-94270\n\n### Steps\n1. Created a cron job scheduled **2 hours in the future** via `openclaw cron add`\n2. Ran `openclaw cron run <job-id> --due` to simulate the fix's default behavior (`mode: \"due\"`)\n3. Ran `openclaw cron run <job-id> --force` to verify the explicit override still works\n\n### Real Gateway Output\n\n**Run with `--due` (fix's default — omitted runMode will send `\"due\"`):**\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"ran\": false,\n  \"reason\": \"not-due\"\n}\n```\n✅ Job correctly refused to execute — schedule guard caught it (2h away = not due).\n\n**Run with `--force` (explicit override — still available):**\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"enqueued\": true\n}\n```\n✅ Immediate execution works when explicitly requested.\n\n### Compatibility Note\nThis PR changes the **agent/MCP tool default only** to `\"due\"`. The Gateway CLI `--force` flag and Gateway RPC remain unchanged. Callers needing immediate execution can pass `runMode: \"force\"` explicitly.\n\n### What was not tested\n- Integration with specific MCP clients (agent tool parameter passing behavior)\n- Gateway upgrade scenario with existing cron jobs",
